      "intent": "Explain the end-to-end funnel that turns a user's topic request into one row in `.regin/topics/topic.json`: an external tool-using agent drafts the JSON+wiki, regin validates and persists it via the ORM, reviewers iterate through revise/regenerate/restore/stop, and a single server-side /diff+/apply path (or the matching library accept/replace/merge helpers) promotes a topic into the approved graph. Also describes the cross-thread cancel machinery that lets a Stop request terminate the agent subprocess without racing the worker's terminal-state writes.",
